name: Inter-specific pollination of Arabidopsis thaliana and Malcolmia littorea
study: Inter-specific pollination of Arabidopsis thaliana and Malcolmia littorea
scoring: Values indicate arbitrary compatibility scores based on the numbers of pollen tubes in the styles: 1: No tubes observed; 2: 1–19 tubes; 3: 20–39 tubes; 4: 40–59 tubes; 5: ≥60 tubes.
growth_conditions: Plant materials were grown in mixed soil in a growth chamber under controlled conditions (light intensity 120–150 µmol m-2s-1, 14-h light/10-h dark cycle at 22 ± 2°C).
eo_definition: "The treatment involving study type in which plants were grown in growth chambers." [GR:pj]
uo_definition: "A dimensionless unit which denotes a simple count of things." [MGED:MGED]
